<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>ENCHANTED CIRCLE CODE OF ETHICS</B></FONT></CENTER>
<P>
The Enchanted Circle is a guild in EverQuest.  Members of the guild bear the name of the guild above their heads in the game, and therefore their actions reflect directly upon the guild.  We want our guild to have a great reputation!
<P>
We have created the following <FONT SIZE=3><B>codes of conduct</B></FONT> for the members of our guild.  We ask that guild members abide by the codes, except in cases of racial hatred or some other motivating factor. Failure to abide by the code will not result in banishment from the guild, but repeated complaints about actions that reflect badly on the guild will.

<BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=4 COLOR=FF2222><B>CODE OF ETHICS</B></FONT><BR>
<UL>
<LI><B>Obey the rules of the game</B> - Play the game by its rules.  Do not exploit bugs, do not use cheats. 
<LI><B>Use proper etiquette</B> - We want people to role-play, we want people to have fun.  Things like kill-stealing do not increase the fun of the game.  Please use good judgement and follow the etiquette of the game.
<LI><B>Protect guild information</B> - Do not distribute information gained from the guild to non-guild members unless given permission.  This includes information about the game and information about other people in the guild.
<LI><B>Protect your guildmates</B> - If you see someone bearing the name of our guild and that person is in trouble, please lend a hand and save their life.  We understand in some cases racial hatred might get in the way and we simply ask that you use good judgement here.
<LI><B>Free binding</B> - For those guild members who have achieved the ability to bind people, please bind guild members for free.  You can expect the same in return.
<LI><B>Jewelry prices</B> - We will be setting guild price ranges for magical jewelry.  We would ask that you sell your jewelry according to our price ranges (these will be set by the guildmembers).  We would also ask you not to compete directly with other guild members when selling wares.  We want the world to feel that buying from a guild member ensures quality and a fair price.  Remember that you represent the guild in these matters.
</UL>
<BR><BR>

